a was postponed due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.framericas.com/articles/2013530-scca-pro-racing-postpones-the-start-of-the-season|title=SCCA Pro Racing Postpones the Start of the Season|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref>  [[Circuit Trois-Rivi\u00e8res]] in Quebec, Canada was scheduled to hold the first international event for the series, but was canceled on 16 April 2020 due to the virus.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.f3americas.com/articles/2012868-f3-americas-championship-makes-international-debut-on-the-streets-of-quebec-in-2020|title=F3 AMERICAS CHAMPIONSHIP MAKES INTERNATIONAL DEBUT ON THE STREETS OF QUEBEC IN 2020|website=F3 Americas Championship|language=en|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.framericas.com/articles/2013620-grand-prix-de-trois-rivieres-update|title=Grand Prix de Trois-Rivi\u00e8res Update|website=F3 Americas Championship|date=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:85%;\"\n! colspan=2| Round\n! Circuit\n! Date\n<!--! Pole Position\n! Fastest Lap\n! Winning Driver\n! Winning Team-->\n! Supporting\n|-\n!rowspan=3| 1\n! R1\n|rowspan=3| [[Circuit of the Americas]], [[Austin, Texas|Austin]]\n|rowspan=3| 5\u20137 June\n|rowspan=3| ''[[2020 Formula 4 United States Championship|Formula 4 United States Championship]]''\n|-\n! R2\n|-\n! R3\n|-\n!rowspan=3| 2\n! R1\n|rowspan=3| [[Virginia International Raceway]], [[Alton, Virginia|Alton]]\n|rowspan=3| 17\u201319 July\n|rowspan=3| ''[[2020 Formula 4 United States Championship|Formula 4 United States Championship]]''<br>''Formula Race Promotions''\n|-\n! R2\n|-\n! R3\n|-\n!rowspan=3| 3\n! R1\n|rowspan=3| [[Barber Motorsports Park]], [[Birmingham, Alabama|Birmingham]]\n|rowspan=3| 31 July\u20132 August\n|rowspan=3| ''[[2020 Formula 4 United States Championship|Formula 4 United States Championship]]''<br>''Radical Cup''\n|-\n! R2\n|-\n! R3\n|-\n!rowspan=3| 4\n! R1\n|rowspan=3| [[